      "author": "goryugocast",
      "description": "## Fixed\n- **CLI API returned empty**: The async `getRelatedNotes` / `getActiveRelatedNotes` yield to the event loop via `setTimeout`, but the Obsidian CLI `eval` command runs code inline and cannot await a Promise that crosses an event-loop tick — so CLI calls returned an empty result. Regression introduced in 0.4.0 (`calculateAsync`).\n\n## Added\n- **Synchronous API for CLI/scripts**: `getRelatedNotesSync(path, options)` and `getActiveRelatedNotesSync(options)`. Same response shape, returned synchronously, so `obsidian eval` reliably receives results. The async variants remain for in-app, UI-non-blocking use.\n- Updated `docs/OBSIDIAN_CLI.md` with `*Sync` usage examples.\n\nVerified against a 16k-note vault: inline `obsidian eval` now returns full JSON results.\n",
      "downloadCount": 3402,
      "draft": false,
